orption rate trend"},{"id":"pm_dom","label":"Permanent market days on market trend"},{"id":"pm_lts","label":"Permanent market list-to-sale ratio"},{"id":"pm_msp","label":"Permanent market price trend"},{"id":"str_occ","label":"STR peak season occupancy rate"},{"id":"str_nr","label":"STR peak season nightly rate"},{"id":"str_rev","label":"STR gross annual revenue"},{"id":"str_off","label":"STR off-season occupancy rate"},{"id":"ret","label":"Retirement and lifestyle migration demand"},{"id":"str_sup","label":"STR supply growth"},{"id":"str_reg","label":"STR regulatory risk"},{"id":"dtd","label":"Drive-to-destination demand driver"},{"id":"seas","label":"Seasonal revenue concentration risk"},{"id":"cap","label":"Cap rate direction"},{"id":"new","label":"New construction pipeline"}],"net_conclusion":"Both permanent residential and STR markets improving. The investment analysis must account for STR supply competition, regulatory risk, and seasonal revenue concentration. Improving headline metrics are real but investor-specific risk narrative is substantial.","commentary":"Scenario 9 is the lake and resort STR scenario requiring analysis of two parallel markets. STR supply growth is counterintuitive but correct as Declining - increased supply creates competitive pressure on per-property revenue even as total market demand grows. The seasonal gap requires Market-Dependent because its impact on value depends on individual investor assumptions. Expert students must recognize that improving headline markets can still carry material investor-specific risks.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors":{"pm_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"4.8 to 2.9 months - crossed from balanced into seller''s territory. Permanent residential market improving."},"pm_dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"38 to 22 days - demand velocity accelerating in the permanent residential market."},"pm_lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"98.4 to 100.8% - crossed above asking price. Permanent residential buyer competition confirmed."},"pm_msp":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"+7.1% - meaningful appreciation in the permanent residential market."},"str_occ":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"71 to 78% peak occupancy - strong demand absorption improvement during the primary revenue season."},"str_nr":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"$218 to $249 (+14.2%) - nightly rate appreciation confirms strong pricing power during peak season."},"str_rev":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"$38,400 to $47,200 annualized (+23%) - strong revenue growth supporting the STR income thesis."},"str_off":{"present":true,"classification":"Stable","rationale":"28 to 31% off-season - modest improvement but materially lower than peak. Revenue concentration remains a structural feature of this market."},"ret":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Documented, verifiable demand driver for the permanent residential market from retirees and lifestyle buyers."},"str_sup":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"41% STR listing growth creates increasing per-property revenue competition. Each listing now competes against more alternatives, a declining signal for per-property revenue trajectory."},"str_reg":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"Oconee County zoning review with potential density limits is active and documented. A material, imminent risk to the STR income model requiring prominent disclosure."},"dtd":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Post-COVID drive-to-destination leisure demand from Charlotte and Atlanta is a documented demand driver for the Lake Hartwell STR market."},"seas":{"present":true,"classification":"Market-Dependent","rationale":"78% peak vs. 31% off-season occupancy means revenue is heavily concentrated in 5 months. The impact on investment value depends on the holding period and financing structure - Market-Dependent is appropriate."},"cap":{"present":false,"rationale":"No cap rate data was provided in this package. This is a distractor."},"new":{"present":false,"rationale":"No new construction data was provided. This is a distractor."}}}'::jsonb
