nsion announced for 2026: approximately 2,800 positions in the $55K-$75K wage range - direct demand driver for suburban workforce housing. New 186-unit apartment complex delivered in in-town Greenville corridor 4 months ago - adding rental supply competitive with in-town submarket. Mortgage rates stabilized at approximately 6.5%. SCDOT infrastructure improvements approved for the Boiling Springs/Lyman corridor. In-town Greenville zoning changes allowing denser residential development approved - potential longer-term supply pressure.","factors":[{"id":"bm_abs","label":"Broad market absorption rate trend"},{"id":"bm_msp","label":"Broad market price trend"},{"id":"sw_abs","label":"Suburban workforce absorption rate trend"},{"id":"sw_dom","label":"Suburban workforce DOM trend"},{"id":"sw_lts","label":"Suburban workforce list-to-sale ratio"},{"id":"sw_rvr","label":"Suburban workforce rental vacancy rate"},{"id":"sw_mrt","label":"Suburban workforce market rent trend"},{"id":"bmw","label":"BMW expansion demand driver (suburban)"},{"id":"scdot","label":"SCDOT infrastructure (suburban corridor)"},{"id":"it_abs","label":"In-town Greenville absorption rate trend"},{"id":"it_dom","label":"In-town Greenville DOM trend"},{"id":"it_rvr","label":"In-town Greenville rental vacancy rate"},{"id":"it_mrt","label":"In-town Greenville market rent trend"},{"id":"apt","label":"New apartment supply (in-town)"},{"id":"rate","label":"Mortgage rate stabilization"},{"id":"zone","label":"In-town zoning density change"},{"id":"it_lts","label":"In-town Greenville list-to-sale ratio"},{"id":"sea","label":"Seasonal demand pattern"},{"id":"str_dem","label":"STR demand"}],"net_conclusion":"Divergent submarket picture. Suburban workforce: strongly improving across all indicators with leading demand drivers. In-town Greenville: softening for-sale and rental, driven by new apartment supply. Investment committee recommendation: allocate capital toward suburban workforce submarket; approach in-town with caution until apartment supply is absorbed.","commentary":"Scenario 10 is the capstone private consulting scenario. Students must synthesize three market data sets, two rental markets, and multiple external factors. Critical skills: (1) recognizing the two submnarkets diverge - in-town moves opposite the broader market; (2) identifying new apartment supply as the proximate driver of in-town deterioration; (3) applying BMW as a suburban-only leading indicator with no in-town impact; and (4) synthesizing all threads into an actionable, submarket-differentiated investment recommendation.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors":{"bm_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"3.8 to 2.7 months - broad market tightening, confirming the subject area improvement is not isolated to one submarket."},"bm_msp":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"+5.7% broad market appreciation - a genuine improving signal confirming overall MSA strength."},"sw_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"3.1 to 2.1 months - crossed into seller''s territory and outperforming the broad market. A positive submarket signal."},"sw_dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"21 to 14 days - demand accelerating in the suburban submarket, outpacing broad market improvement."},"sw_lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"99.8 to 102.4% - crossed above asking price. Buyers competing in the suburban workforce submarket."},"sw_rvr":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"4.2 to 2.9% - extremely tight rental demand. Strong income thesis for the suburban submarket."},"sw_mrt":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"$1,340 to $1,410/mo (+5.2%) - meaningful rent growth alongside the for-sale appreciation. Both investment dimensions improving."},"bmw":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"2,800 announced positions in the $55K-$75K wage band are a leading indicator of near-term demand growth in the suburban workforce price range. Direct alignment."},"scdot":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Approved roadway improvements are a long-term positive signal for the suburban corridor - documented public investment supporting neighborhood trajectory."},"it_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"2.8 to 4.1 months - softening in the in-town submarket, moving opposite to both the broad market and the suburban submarket. A clear divergence."},"it_dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"22 to 31 days - homes sitting longer in the in-town submarket while the rest of the market tightens."},"it_rvr":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"6.8 to 8.4% - rising rental vacancy in the in-town submarket confirming the softening on the income side."},"it_mrt":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"$1,290 to $1,280/mo - mild but confirmed rent softening concurrent with the for-sale softening."},"apt":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"186-unit complex delivered 4 months ago is the proximate driver of the in-town rental vacancy increase and rent softening. Direct, documented competitive supply impact."},"rate":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Rates stabilized at 6.5% after prior increases - a modest but real affordability improvement supporting broad and suburban demand."},"zone":{"present":true,"classification":"Market-Dependent","rationale":"Approved denser development in the Augusta Road corridor could add future supply pressure. Directionally uncertain on a longer-term horizon - real but not yet reflected in closed data."},"it_lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"101.2 to 99.8% - losing the over-ask premium in the in-town submarket while the suburban market is gaining it."},"sea":{"present":false,"rationale":"No seasonal data was provided. This is a distractor."},"str_dem":{"present":false,"rationale":"No STR data was provided for this market. This is a distractor."}}}'::jsonb
