  '',
  '{"subject":{"address_summary":"4418 Reidville Road, Greer, SC 29650","subject_summary":"3BR/2BA, 1,820 SF, built 2002, ranch - partial take of 0.18 acres · Reidville corridor","school":"Spartanburg County School District 6","effective_date":"Current - date of taking","context_label":"Government & Public Use Context","context_text":"SCDOT condemnation appraisal. SCDOT is acquiring a portion of a residential property for the I-85 ramp improvement project near Greer. You must: (1) define the appropriate market area; (2) analyze general market conditions; and (3) identify and address any project influence on market data."},"tables":[{"label":"","cols":["Indicator","Prior 7-12 Months","Current 1-6 Months"],"rows":[["Closed Sales (1-mile radius)","28","24"],["Active Listings","9","12"],["Median Days on Market","32","38"],["Median Sale Price","$231,500","$228,800"],["List-to-Sale Price Ratio","98.1%","96.9%"],["Absorption Rate","4.2 months","5.1 months"]]}],"external":"The I-85 ramp improvement project was publicly announced 8 months ago. Market participants have documented buyer hesitation for properties immediately adjacent to the project corridor.","factors":[{"id":"abs","label":"Absorption rate trend"},{"id":"dom","label":"Days on market trend"},{"id":"lts","label":"List-to-sale price ratio trend"},{"id":"msp","label":"Median sale price trend"},{"id":"inv","label":"Active listing inventory level"},{"id":"proj","label":"SCDOT project announcement influence"},{"id":"post","label":"Post-taking market recovery data"},{"id":"sea","label":"Seasonal demand pattern"}],"net_conclusion":"Softening/declining market as of the date of taking with project influence as a contributing factor. The condemnation appraiser must separately analyze general market conditions and project-specific influence under SC condemnation standards.","commentary":"Scenario 3 introduces the project influence doctrine. SC condemnation law requires analyzing market conditions as if the project were not in place - meaning project-influenced data must be identified, acknowledged, and potentially bracketed or adjusted. The post-taking distractor reinforces the retrospective hard wall in the condemnation context.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors":{"abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"Rose from 4.2 to 5.1 months as of the date of taking. A present, contemporaneous declining signal in the market data."},"dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"Rose from 32 to 38 days - demand softening as of the taking date."},"lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"98.1 to 96.9% - mild but present declining signal in the contemporaneous data."},"msp":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"-1.2% slight price softening confirmed in the data package as of the taking date."},"inv":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"Rose from 9 to 12 actives - building supply reinforcing the softening picture."},"proj":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"Announced 8 months before the taking with documented buyer hesitation for adjacent properties. A real, present project influence factor that must be identified and addressed under SC condemnation standards."},"post":{"present":false,"rationale":"CRITICAL DISTRACTOR: Post-taking data is inadmissible. The hard wall for condemnation analysis is the date of taking."},"sea":{"present":false,"rationale":"No seasonal data was provided. This is a distractor."}}}'::jsonb
