roject influence"},{"id":"post","label":"Post-taking market recovery data"},{"id":"sea","label":"Seasonal demand pattern"}],"net_conclusion":"Two-layer declining market. General market without project: moderate decline driven by rate pressure. Corridor with project influence: severe decline - absorption approaching buyer''s market, prices 3.4% below prior period. The broader market data is the required without-project baseline under SC condemnation law.","commentary":"Scenario 5 introduces the two-layer condemnation analysis. The core skill is distinguishing general market decline (visible in both data sets) from project-specific influence (visible only in the corridor data divergence). The broader market provides the required without-project baseline. The 53% DOM divergence is the most defensible quantification of project influence.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
