nd pattern"}],"net_conclusion":"Strongly improving rural corridor market. The rural corridor is the appropriate controlling market area for USDA analysis. Fiber internet demand is the proximate cause of the improvement.","commentary":"The methodological distractor - using the adjacent suburban market as controlling - tests whether students understand that the appropriate market area for a USDA rural property is the rural competitive market. The suburban data is more abundant and strongly improving, making it a seductive but incorrect choice. USDA appraisal requires using data that actually represents the competitive market for the subject property.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
