te and general market pressure"},{"id":"const","label":"Active construction disruption factor"},{"id":"post","label":"Post-construction market recovery"},{"id":"sea","label":"Seasonal demand pattern"}],"net_conclusion":"Two-layer declining market. Background without project: moderate decline under rate and employment pressure. SC-9 corridor: severe decline - absorption halted, prices 8.8% below prior period vs. 1.8% in background. The excess corridor deterioration beyond background conditions is attributable to project influence.","commentary":"The SCDOT acquisition comparable pattern introduces a nuanced condemnation issue: SCDOT-negotiated acquisitions may contaminate the comparable sales pool. Students must identify this as Market-Dependent because its directional impact depends on whether those transactions were above or below arm''s length value - a question the appraiser must investigate, not assume.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
