:"fema","label":"FEMA map expansion and flood insurance cost burden"},{"id":"fha_fi","label":"FHA flood insurance requirement"},{"id":"gm_ctrl","label":"General market as the controlling market area"},{"id":"sea","label":"Seasonal demand pattern"}],"net_conclusion":"Divergent market. General Greenville County: strongly improving. Flood zone submarket: declining due to FEMA map expansion and mandatory insurance cost burden. Controlling market area: flood zone submarket. FHA designation: DECLINING.","commentary":"The methodological distractor - using the strong general market - is particularly seductive because the general market data is so clearly positive. FEMA map expansion creating a new insurance cost burden creates a distinct submarket with its own demand characteristics. Using the general market would produce an incorrect FHA Increasing designation, creating lender compliance exposure and potential harm to the buyer.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
