  'You are appraising the property at 3812 SC-101, Woodruff, SC 29388 (3BR/2BA, 1,760 SF, built 2008, vinyl ranch - partial take: 0.24 acres; remainder: 0.38 acres with dwelling; VA loan balance approximately $181,000 · SC-101 corridor). Combined VA appraisal and SCDOT condemnation on the same property. Two analytical frameworks operate on the same underlying data simultaneously. VA framework: uses general market data (without-project baseline) to assess remainder property marketability. SCDOT framework: uses project influence doctrine - the divergence between general and corridor data quantifies the project impact. The two conclusions are not contradictory; they answer different questions. Section 6 — Market Analysis — requires you to identify which market indicators and external factors are present in the data package, classify each present indicator as Improving, Stable, Declining, or Market-Dependent based on the indicator data and external context, and write a market-supported rationale citing specific data from the indicator table or external context. Indicators not evidenced in the data package must be left unchecked. Every classification must be grounded in specific evidence — this assignment evaluates evidence-based market analysis, not pattern recognition or reflexive checklist behavior.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S6-C5';

