et inventory level"},{"id":"c_abs","label":"Corridor absorption rate trend"},{"id":"c_dom","label":"Corridor days on market trend"},{"id":"c_msp","label":"Corridor price trend"},{"id":"c_lts","label":"Corridor list-to-sale ratio trend"},{"id":"proj","label":"SCDOT project announcement influence"},{"id":"bmw","label":"BMW expansion and general market demand driver"},{"id":"rate","label":"Mortgage rate stabilization"},{"id":"va_ltv","label":"VA loan-to-value concern"},{"id":"scdot_c","label":"SCDOT acquisition comparables"},{"id":"sea","label":"Seasonal demand pattern"}],"net_conclusion":"Two-framework analysis on the same data. VA conclusion: general market improving - supports remainder property marketability and loan balance security. SCDOT conclusion: corridor declining severely due to project influence - the general market is the without-project baseline and the divergence quantifies the project impact. These conclusions are not contradictory; they answer different questions.","commentary":"Scenario 10 requires operating two analytical frameworks simultaneously on the same underlying data. The critical insight: the VA conclusion (general market improving) and the SCDOT conclusion (corridor declining due to project influence) are not contradictory - they address different questions. The without-project baseline is what the VA uses; the project influence divergence is what SCDOT addresses. Expert students must articulate both clearly without conflating them.","classification_options":["Improving","Stable","Declining","Market-Dependent"],"min_rationale_chars":20}'::jsonb,
  '{"factors":{"gm_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"4.1 to 3.2 months in the general market - improving. This is the VA framework data set supporting remainder property marketability and the SCDOT without-project baseline."},"gm_dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"26 to 19 days in the general market - demand accelerating. Supports VA conclusion that market conditions are favorable for the remainder property."},"gm_lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"99.4 to 101.2% - crossed above asking price in the general market. VA market condition conclusion: improving."},"gm_msp":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"+5.7% general market appreciation. Without project influence, market conditions support the remainder property value relative to the VA loan balance."},"gm_inv":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"28 to 21 actives - tightening supply confirming the improving general market picture."},"c_abs":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"5.2 to 14.1 months in the corridor - a dramatic shift. For the SCDOT framework, this severe corridor deterioration vs. 3.2 months general market quantifies the project influence."},"c_dom":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"34 to 58 days in the corridor vs. 19 days in the general market. The 39-day excess corridor DOM is a documented project influence signal."},"c_msp":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"-4.2% in the corridor vs. +5.7% in the general market. The nearly 10 percentage point divergence quantifies the project-specific price impact for the SCDOT framework."},"c_lts":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"93.1% in the corridor vs. 101.2% in the general market. Sellers in the corridor accepting 8+ percentage points below asking while general market buyers bid above asking."},"proj":{"present":true,"classification":"Declining","rationale":"18-month announcement with active ROW acquisition underway. Documented buyer avoidance creates the divergence between general and corridor data that quantifies project influence under the SCDOT framework."},"bmw":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"BMW expansion is a documented positive leading indicator for the general market - supporting the VA framework conclusion about remainder property value trajectory."},"rate":{"present":true,"classification":"Improving","rationale":"Stabilized rates are a modest positive general market signal supporting the VA market condition conclusion."},"va_ltv":{"present":false,"rationale":"DISTRACTOR: Loan-to-value analysis is a valuation and underwriting conclusion, not a market condition indicator. The market condition analysis informs the value conclusion; it does not include the LTV calculation."},"scdot_c":{"present":false,"rationale":"DISTRACTOR: Whether SCDOT acquisition transactions are appropriate as comparables is a comparable selection and verification issue, not a market condition indicator."},"sea":{"present":false,"rationale":"No seasonal data was provided. This is a distractor."}}}'::jsonb
